================================================================================
DEPENDENCY LICENSES
================================================================================

This project incorporates and builds upon the following open-source projects,
which are licensed under their respective terms:

1. MAME (Multi Arcade Machine Emulator)
   - License: GPL-2.0
   - Used as behavioral reference for chip implementations
   - https://github.com/mamedev/mame

2. fx68k (68000 soft core)
   - Author: Jorge Cwik (ijor)
   - License: MIT
   - https://github.com/ijor/fx68k

3. T80 (Z80 soft core)
   - License: LGPL
   - Used in audio CPU implementations

4. TG68K (68020 soft core)
   - Author: Tobias Gubener
   - License: LGPL/CC0
   - https://github.com/TobiFlex/TG68K.C

5. MiSTer sys/ framework
   - License: GPL-2.0
   - Authors: MiSTer-devel team
   - Components: HPS interface, video scaler, SDRAM controller framework
   - https://github.com/MiSTer-devel/Template_MiSTer

6. TaitoF2_MiSTer
   - Author: wickerwaka
   - License: GPL-2.0
   - Support chips: TC0260DAR, TC0140SYT, TC0220IOC
   - https://github.com/wickerwaka/TaitoF2_MiSTer

================================================================================
SPECIAL NOTES ON ORIGINAL RTL
================================================================================

The RTL in chips/ contains original implementations of arcade hardware based on:
- MAME source code analysis (behavioral reference only)
- Hardware decap analysis and datasheets where available
- Community-contributed disassemblies and hardware research

We do NOT copy MAME or other projects' code. Each RTL module is written from
scratch to match documented hardware behavior and datasheet specifications.

